theorem Topology.P1_inter_of_isOpen_left {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) (hP1B : Topology.P1 B) :
    Topology.P1 (A ∩ B) := by
  unfold Topology.P1 at *
  intro x hxAB
  -- Decompose the membership information
  have hxA : x ∈ A := hxAB.1
  have hxB : x ∈ B := hxAB.2
  -- From `P1` for `B`, obtain `x ∈ closure (interior B)`
  have hx_closureB : x ∈ closure (interior B) := hP1B hxB
  -- We will show that `x ∈ closure (A ∩ interior B)`
  have hx_closureAIntB : x ∈ closure (A ∩ interior B) := by
    -- Characterize closure via neighbourhood intersections
    have h_mem_closureB := (mem_closure).1 hx_closureB
    -- Use the neighbourhood criterion to build the desired membership
    refine (mem_closure).2 ?_
    intro U hU hxU
    -- Consider the open neighbourhood `U ∩ A` of `x`
    have hUA_open : IsOpen (U ∩ A) := hU.inter hA
    have hxUA : x ∈ U ∩ A := And.intro hxU hxA
    -- Apply the closure property of `interior B`
    rcases h_mem_closureB (U ∩ A) hUA_open hxUA with ⟨y, hy⟩
    -- Split the obtained membership information
    have hyU : y ∈ U := hy.1.1
    have hyA : y ∈ A := hy.1.2
    have hyIntB : y ∈ interior B := hy.2
    -- Assemble a point in `U ∩ (A ∩ interior B)`
    exact ⟨y, And.intro hyU (And.intro hyA hyIntB)⟩
  -- For an open set `A`, `interior (A ∩ B) = A ∩ interior B`
  have hInt_eq : interior (A ∩ B) = A ∩ interior B := by
    have h := interior_inter A B
    simpa [hA.interior_eq] using h
  -- Rewrite and conclude
  simpa [hInt_eq] using hx_closureAIntB

theorem Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A := by
  exact closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
